file_content.text: Spaceport traffic is well under control.
I can't be of much more assistance. You'll have to speak to Captain Golah.
Welcome to Tatooine, all of you. If you hold a moment, I can provide directions to the research center.
My lord, welcome to Tatooine. If you hold a moment, I can provide directions to the research center.
Welcome to Tatooine, sir. If you hold a moment, I can provide directions to the research center.
Ah--another mercenary. If you hold a moment, I can provide directions to the research center.
I wasn't aware of any research center.
Research center?
There's some mistake.
You're--sorry. My error.
Much of the Imperial traffic we get is assigned to the archaeological expedition. Security, scientific equipment--they don't tell me what it's for.
If you're going to be here long, you... might wish to consult with Captain Golah. We wouldn't want to interfere with Sith activity.
In any case, if you're looking for work, you might want to speak to Captain Golah.
If you're going to be here long, you might wish to speak to Captain Golah. Ensure that our operations don't overlap.
I'll pay your captain a visit.
I'll keep that in mind.
Thank you.
These are the center's coordinates. I'll alert them that you may be coming.
It's not your place to make suggestions.
You're out of line.
You could not comprehend my purpose here.
Fool.
Understood. I'll, ah--I'm doing the best I can to anticipate your needs, my lord.
Do not question me or my mission. Understand?
You're out of line.
Of course. I'm, ah, simply trying to anticipate your needs.
I'm not interested in what you think. I'm here for a job.
Don't give me suggestions.
Huh. Carry on, then.
Go on, then.
Of course. Coordinates are here, in Mos Ila proper. I'll let Captain Golah know to expect you.
Please move along. I'm waiting for a shipment for the forward camp.
